Painting, in watercolour and tin alloy on cardboard, two men in combat with clubs, possibly (from the inscription) Ushna, a descendent of Puru, and Jayadratha (an ally of the Kauravas in the Mahabharata).
Painted in watercolour and tin alloy on cardboard
Bonita Trust Indian Paintings Cataloguing Project
Painting, two men in combat, watercolour and tin alloy on cardboard, Kalighat, Kolkata, ca. 1890
Two men in combat with clubs, possibly (from the inscription) Ushna, a descendent of Puru, and Jayadratha (an ally of the Kauravas).
